z), steamed broccoli, ¾ of the reserved grated cheese (approx. 5 oz), yogurt, butter, milk, salt, pepper and paprika into mixing bowl and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. Adjust seasoning and if necessary mix a further <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Brush the outside of potato skins with oil and sprinkle with salt, for a crispier skin."},{"content":"Spoon potato mixture into potato skin shells. Bake potatoes for 20 minutes (375°F), then top with remaining grated cheese and bake for 5-10 minutes (375°F) or until cheese melts. Garnish with chopped chives and serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To scoop out potato flesh, use a paring knife to score the potato halves, leaving a border (approx. ¼ in. thick). Then use a spoon to carefuly scoop out the flesh.","If potato skin is compromised or too thin to hold the filling, create a foil boat by scrunching a strip of foil and shaping around the potato skin before adding filling.","Make the potato mixture ahead and stuff the shells just before baking.","Garnish with sour cream or plain yogurt."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 25m","4 pieces"]}